    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <head>462. Memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName> to the
                    Attorney General, <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName>, and General <persName corresp="#p_TGMD_1"
                        >Taylor</persName>, October 30<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d462fn1"
                        >Information on intelligence collecting infiltration and guerrilla warfare
                        teams. Secret. 1 p. Kennedy Library, <gloss target="#t_NSF_1">NSF</gloss>,
                        Countries Series, Cuba, Subjects, Intelligence Materials,
                        10/1/62–11/12/62.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-10-30">October 30, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d462-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d462-1"/>
                <p>This is to advise you that there are at the present time 20 intelligence
                    collecting infiltration and guerrilla warfare teams who have been carefully
                    trained and equipped with communication facilities available for such use as the
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss> may indicate. These teams are all
                    Cubans, there are no Americans or other foreign nationals included, they have
                    been carefully selected by men familiar with the Cuban community and the
                    tradecrafts involved and are ready to go. In addition there are a number of
                    others who are partially trained that could be brought to a reasonable level of
                    efficiency in a short time.</p>
                <p>At a meeting on 26 October it was decided that General <persName
                        corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName> would determine <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss> requirements from General <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJF_1">Carroll</persName> and State requirements for political
                    information from Secretary <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Alexis
                        Johnson</persName> and then determine what resources were available and what
                    actions would be desirable to accomplish the needed results. <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss> is awaiting word from General <persName
                        corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName>. In the meantime, with General
                        <persName corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName>’s concurrence, <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss> has taken steps to inform <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCLANT_1">CINCLANT</gloss> and several other Commands of the
                    availability of the above assets.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_MJA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">John A. McCone</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <affiliation>Director</affiliation>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
